page.title: 09THE DOCKS
page.content: This is the Dock that's slack-built, This is the lock that was made for the dock that was slack built. This is the silt that supported the lock that was made forthe dock that's slack-built. This is the water that scoured the silt that supported the lock that was made for the dock that's slack-built.... This is King's Lynn that crowed in the morn To see old Guy of his glory shorn. Who mourned with the merchant and all forlorn, When they found the engineer laughed to corn, For planning a bottom eroded and torn, Without any concrete,to hold the water,that scoured the silt,that supported the lock,that was made for the dock that's slack-built.
